'''Spain''' participated in the '''Eurovision Song Contest 2003''' with an entry selected through the second series of the reality-show [[Operaci<U+00F3>n Triunfo]]. [[Beth (musician)|Beth]] with the song "[[Dime (song)|Dime]]", composed by Jes<U+00FA>s Mar<U+00ED>a P<U+00E9>rez and Amaya Mart<U+00ED>nez, was chosen through televoting by the Spanish public. At Eurovision, Beth placed 8th with 81 points. 

== National Final ==
After the regular final of Operaci<U+00F3>n Triunfo (where [[Ainhoa Cantalapiedra]] was declared the overall winner), the top 3 contestants - Ainhoa herself, Manuel Carrasco, and Beth - qualified for the Eurovision phase of the contest, which consisted of a semi-final and a final. Three songs were assigned to each contestant among those submitted to national broadcaster [[Televisi<U+00F3>n Espa<U+00F1>ola|TVE]], making a total of nine songs. <ref>http://www.portalmix.com/operaciontriunfo2/resumengala/030210.shtml</ref> In the semi-final, a jury eliminated one of the songs assigned to each artist, and then a finalist song was chosen for each contestant though televoting. The three songs that participated in the final were the following <ref>http://www.portalmix.com/operaciontriunfo2/resumengala/030217.shtml</ref><ref>http://www.esc-history.com/nf-entries.asp?country=Spain&year=2003&order=ItemNr</ref>:

